      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e If you want to shoot yourself in the foot, we should block it?\n\nYes.  There\u0027s no place where this call would be a reasonable thing to do.\n\n\u003e Where does it stop?\n\nI don\u0027t think we ever stop.  Always make things more user friendly to within what the specs allow?  Are you worried about getting a bunch of error handling code?  In the context of this commit, that doesn\u0027t seem too worrisome, it\u0027s 3 lines.  If it were 100 lines of complex error handling I might feel differently.\n\n\u003e  isn\u0027t there cases where you might want to delete your own account?\n\nCan you talk more to this?  I can\u0027t think of a valid case where you\u0027d want to delete/disable your own account, but if they exist, yes, that would invalidate this patch.",
